    "narrative": "Our lineup today is anchored by **Cal Raleigh** (70.13) and **Geraldo Perdomo** (69.13), who stand as our most confident plays. **Cal Raleigh** benefits significantly from hitting second against the hittable Liberatore, gaining an 8% boost for the premium spot in the order. Meanwhile, **Geraldo Perdomo** is a critical asset; despite a minor platoon disadvantage, his position atop the order against the high-xERA Germ\u00e1n M\u00e1rquez provides him the highest SP-skill leverage of the day, making him essential for both scoring and potential stolen base production. **Will Smith** (68.08) also earns a strong recommendation, bolstered by favorable wind conditions at his park and a high-upside matchup against Colin Rea.\n\nThe decision to bench **Yainer Diaz** (51.72) was our most difficult call. While **Yainer Diaz** carries a respectable projection, he fell just short of our threshold due to the optimizer assuming a lower spot in the batting order, which heavily penalizes his run-scoring ceiling. Conversely, we are keeping **Taylor Ward** (59.23) and **Jos\u00e9 Ram\u00edrez** (59.86) active despite some volatility. **Taylor Ward** is buoyed by a significant 16% park factor boost that offsets a tough matchup against the elite Crochet, while **Jos\u00e9 Ram\u00edrez** remains a must-start despite a negative BvP history and a tough draw against Gausman, as his base projection simply carries too much weight to ignore.\n\nWe must remain vigilant regarding the \"Lineup Pending\" designations across the board. Most notably, **Jonathan Aranda** (63.78) is riding a high 12% boost from a favorable platoon matchup against Bailey Ober, but if he hits lower than the assumed #3 spot, that efficiency will erode quickly. Additionally, while we are chasing SB upside with **Jung Hoo Lee** (52.15) and **Matt Chapman** (55.81), both are facing the stingy Eury P\u00e9rez. We have managed the bench to preserve our game caps, keeping guys like **Gleyber Torres** and **Drew Gilbert** in reserve to ensure we don't bleed efficiency on marginal starts that lack high-leverage context.",
